message.content:
Primary programming language: PHP

Primary development framework: Laravel (Laravel framework, project uses laravel/framework ^11.28)

Why:
- composer.json (project dependency manifest) requires "php": "^8.3" and "laravel/framework": "^11.28", which identifies PHP as the language and Laravel as the framework.
- The repository layout and files match a Laravel app: presence of artisan, app/, bootstrap/, config/, public/, resources/, routes/, storage/, and database/ are standard Laravel structure.
- Additional Laravel packages are present (laravel/breeze, laravel/telescope, laravel/horizon, laravel/sanctum), reinforcing that this is a Laravel application.

(Note: composer.json description string says "Laravel 10.x blog" but the actual dependency lists laravel/framework ^11.28 â€” the dependency definition is the authoritative indicator of the installed framework version.)
